Iran on Tuesday announced 122 new deaths from the novel coronavirus, raising the official toll to 1,934 in one of the world’s worst hit countries. Health ministry spokesman Kianoush Jahanpour said a record 1,762 new cases have been confirmed in Iran over the past 24 hours and 24,811 people are now known to have been infected. More details to follow….. AFP Coronavirus: Iranian MP ‘dies of flu’ as death toll rises to 43 in Iran Iran reports 54 new coronavirus deaths, highest one-day toll Qatar confirms first coronavirus case